s": [20, 24], "text": "AMD"}, {"indices": [108, 113], "text": "FUTU"}], "urls": [], "user_mentions": []}, "quoted_tweet": {"type": "tweet", "id": "2049671960267989328", "url": "https://x.com/dannycheng2022/status/2049671960267989328", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/dannycheng2022/status/2049671960267989328", "text": "$AMD (April 30, 2026-monthly chart)\n\nOver the past few days, as $AMD pulled back from its all-time high, several friends and influencers have trimmed their positions. It served as a timely reminder that many are still trading in and out \u2014 a mindset that often causes them to miss the much larger long-term rally.\n\nNo doubt, locking in profits totally makes sense, but true long-term wealth is NEVER built through constant short-term trading.\n\nZooming out on the monthly chart (panel 2), the green light recently flipped to red on the latest bar. Historically, this signal has often preceded multi-month uptrends. \n\nWith this powerful GOD candle now in place, I expect (1) many traders will take profits while (2) retail investors who missed the move will not chase, fearing they\u2019re buying the top.\n\nThankfully, our community was well-positioned for this. I first highlighted buys at $110 and continued adding non-stop all the way to $200. \n\nUnfortunately, I didn\u2019t manage to perfectly time the absolute bottom at $76. Fortunately, holding a strong position of 24,888 shares is more than enough to ride the whale momentum going forward.\n\nPosition sizing matters far more than timing the perfect bottom. Timing the perfect bottom is nice, but it\u2019s meaningless without sufficient size. A well-sized position in a strong trend will almost always outperform perfect timing with a tiny allocation.\n\nThe whales gave us nearly a full year to accumulate. At the end of the day, long-term investing demands discipline, strong holding power in the right names, and the buying power to keep adding during dips. That combination is what drives true compound gains. \n\n@cantonmeow \n@matthughes13 \n@chad_ventures \n@redfoxryder", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 10, "replyCount": 9, "likeCount": 191, "quoteCount": 3, "viewCount": 66394, "createdAt": "Thu Apr 30 02:07:31 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 26, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2049671960267989328", "displayTextRange": [0, 279], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "dannycheng2022", "url": "https://x.com/dannycheng2022", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/dannycheng2022", "id": "1563185751051091970", "name": "Danny cheng", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1743158140693307392/DPUD0fa3_normal.jpg", "coverPicture": "", "description": "", "location": "Hong Kong", "followers": 80179, "following": 550, "status": "", "canDm": true, "canMediaTag": true, "createdAt": "Fri Aug 26 15:25:13 +0000 2022", "entities": {"description": {"urls": []}, "url": {}}, "fastFollowersCount": 0, "favouritesCount": 50423, "hasCustomTimelines": true, "isTranslator": false, "mediaCount": 10729, "statusesCount": 40983, "withheldInCountries": [], "affiliatesHighlightedLabel": {}, "possiblySensitive": false, "pinnedTweetIds": ["1815738260951625979"], "profile_bio": {"description": "Tsla, pltr and nvdia investor. I use my homily charts for investing. Not financial advice. Tesla car owner, piano self learner. Don\u2019t follow me as I\u2019m stupid.", "entities": {"description": {}, "url": {"urls": [{"display_url": "patreon.com/DannyTrades", "expanded_url": "https://www.patreon.com/DannyTrades", "indices": [0, 23], "url": "https://t.co/iB4xJha2Xd"}]}}}, "isAutomated": false, "automatedBy": null}, "extendedEntities": {"media": [{"allow_download_status": {"allow_download": true}, "display_url": "pic.twitter.com/CnIFZ3dxvV", "expanded_url": "https://twitter.com/dannycheng2022/status/204967196026798932